<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="127.[151,1437,153,1151]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,224,251]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A small species very similar in general colouration to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[944,1048,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitalisi" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[944,1048,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">P. vitalisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1057,1188,225,251]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1057,1181,225,251]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">comb. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differing primarily in that the orange lateral and sutural margins extend around the elytral apex; T7, 8 dark brown and lateral margins of 
<date box="[151,188,297,323]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V6</date>
, and lateral and posterior margins of 
<date box="[599,636,297,323]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V7</date>
, narrowly dark brown. One of four 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[1030,1165,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1165,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have an aedeagal sheath sternite terminated by a boomerang shaped piece, and in which the aedeagus is wider across the middle and the membranous apical portions of the LL are wider at their bases than at their apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="127.[151,1437,153,1151]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,405,431]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Male</emphasis>
. 6.1 mm long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[529,805,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 374−381" captionStartId="126.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,638,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,638,1889]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURES 374−381. Pygoluciola bangladeshi sp. nov. type males. 374, 376 habitus dorsal (376 pronotum and anterior portion of elytra only); 375 habitus ventral; 377 aedeagal sheath ventral (arrows indicate hairy lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite; 378, 379 aedeagus: 378 dorsal, 379 ventral; 380, 381: abdomen: 380 ventral; 381 dorsal. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508246" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508246/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Figs 374−376, 380, 381</figureCitation>
): pronotum orange with underlying fat body irregularly retracted; MN and MS orange; elytra very dark brown with orange lateral and sutural margins which extend around the elytral apex; venter of thorax dark brown, legs orange yellow with dark brown tibiae and tarsi; ventrites anterior to LO brown; abdominal tergites brown, T7, 8 darker brown than preceding tergites. Pronotum: subparallel sided (A=B=C); width &lt;humeral width. Elytron: subparallel sided, 
<date box="[850,885,548,575]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">5 x</date>
as long as median pronotal length. Head: GHW/ SIW 5/1; ASD &lt;ASW sockets are not contiguous; antennae shorter than 
<date box="[956,990,585,611]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">2 x</date>
GHW, segments simple elongate longer than wide, pedicel with basal constriction. Mouthparts: apical labial palpomere laterally flattened like a broad triangle with inner margin dentate (2–3 teeth). Abdomen: LO in 
<date box="[833,867,657,683]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V6</date>
retracted slightly from sides which are dark brown; LO in 
<date box="[225,259,693,719]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">V7</date>
retracted narrowly from sides and posterior margin; MPP short, broad and apically rounded; T8 parallel sided with anterolateral arms elongate slender, not bearing membranous projection on inner ventral surface; rounded posterior margin does not incline ventrally.Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[829,927,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURES 374−381" captionStartId="126.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,638,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,638,1889]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURES 374−381. Pygoluciola bangladeshi sp. nov. type males. 374, 376 habitus dorsal (376 pronotum and anterior portion of elytra only); 375 habitus ventral; 377 aedeagal sheath ventral (arrows indicate hairy lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite; 378, 379 aedeagus: 378 dorsal, 379 ventral; 380, 381: abdomen: 380 ventral; 381 dorsal. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508246" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508246/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Fig. 377</figureCitation>
): sternite expanding gradually with wide apex terminated by a ‘boomerang’ shaped hairy piece. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[837,995,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 374−381" captionStartId="126.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[157,1435,638,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@126.[151,1435,638,1889]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURES 374−381. Pygoluciola bangladeshi sp. nov. type males. 374, 376 habitus dorsal (376 pronotum and anterior portion of elytra only); 375 habitus ventral; 377 aedeagal sheath ventral (arrows indicate hairy lobes arising from boomerang shaped piece at apex of sheath sternite; 378, 379 aedeagus: 378 dorsal, 379 ventral; 380, 381: abdomen: 380 ventral; 381 dorsal. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508246" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508246/files/figure.png" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Fig. 378, 379</figureCitation>
): approximately twice as long as wide; basal sclerotized section of LL widest across area where the membranous parts of the LL arise, only slightly separated along their middorsal length and with base asymmetrical, produced strongly to left; ML reaching just beyond basal portion; apical membranous sections of LL wider at base than at apex; well defined hairy membranous sausage shaped lobes arising from ventral surface just behind inner origins of membranous sections of LL; membranous apical portion of LL shorter than basal sclerotized portion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="128" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="127.[151,1437,153,1151]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1017,1043]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Ho, 2019" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" box="[324,606,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bangladeshi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,606,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Pygoluciola bangladeshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[615,709,1017,1043]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,702,1017,1043]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is one of four species presently assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[1223,1358,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1223,1358,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where the aedeagal and sheath morphology are suggestive of the related genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ballantyne Lambkin &amp; Fu" authorityYear="2013" box="[968,1094,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Abscondita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[968,1094,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Abscondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and where the sheath sternite is terminated by a boomerang shaped section. The elytral colour pattern is similar to that described for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bugnion" authorityYear="1922" box="[1304,1437,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicollieri">
<emphasis box="[1304,1437,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">L. nicollieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[213,322,1125,1151]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bugnion" box="[337,502,1125,1151]" firstAuthor="Bugnion" pageId="127" pageNumber="128" pagination="1 - 14" refId="ref115657" refString="Bugnion, E. (1922) Luciola nicollieri sp. n. de Ceylan. Spolia Zeylandica, XII, 1 - 14." type="journal article" year="1922">Bugnion 1922</bibRefCitation>
). We are presently unable to locate a 
<typeStatus box="[919,967,1125,1151]" pageId="127" pageNumber="128">type</typeStatus>
for the latter.
</paragraph>
